.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-INSTALL-ASSETS 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-install-assets \- install bundled assistant assets
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch install-assets
[\fBclaude-agents\fR|\fBclaude-skills\fR|\fBcodex-skills\fR]
[\fB\-\-filter\fR \fIPATTERN\fR...]
[\fB\-\-force\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B install-assets
installs bundled assistant assets into the current repository.
.TP
.B claude-agents
Install into
.BR .claude/agents/ .
.TP
.B claude-skills
Install into
.BR .claude/skills/ .
Required bundled Claude agents for those skills are installed too.
.TP
.B codex-skills
Install into
.BR .agents/skills/ .
The shared internal drafter brief is written to
.BR .agents/internal/commit-message-drafter.md .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I GROUP
Install only one bundled asset group. If omitted, install every group.
.TP
.BI "\-\-filter " PATTERN "..."
Install only bundled assets whose entry names match gitignore-style patterns.
.TP
.B \-\-force
Overwrite an existing installed asset.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1)
